# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# quite_change/ — .gitignore  (supplements the parent repo .gitignore)
#
# PUSH POLICY: code + the minimal config needed to RUN the pipeline ONLY.
# Do NOT push: flash reports (provided separately), packets, classification
# outputs, HTML/CSV deliverables, logs, caches, backups, empty/scratch files.
#
# NOTE: gitignore does NOT support inline comments — every pattern is on its
# own line, every comment on its own line.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Secrets (reinforces parent)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Reports / heavy data — provided to the senior separately, never committed
# (決算短信 PDFs + text + SQLite index, ~1 GB)
data/flash_reports/
# old R+ web-research fixtures (not used by this pipeline)
data/parser_outputs/
# old R+ / sector deliverable data
data/company_research_*.json
data/it_staged_additions/

# Everything in data/quarterly/ (packets, outputs, cached PDFs, batch dumps,
# tdnet DB, backups, AND the regenerable per-year target lists — select_year.py
# rebuilds those). Nothing here is needed to ship the code.
data/quarterly/

# Old sector-verification effort (separate from the quarterly pipeline)
verification_batches/

# Outputs / deliverables — regenerated by the run, not pushed
# (all rendered views incl. the research/static UI)
*.html
*.jsonl
deliverables/**/*.csv
deliverables/**/*.json

# Result / report / planning docs — NOT required to run the pipeline.
# Keep ONLY README.md (the run guide). Everything else (SENIOR_SUMMARY,
# BUCKET_PROPOSAL, audit findings, NOTES, *_PLAN.md, etc.) is excluded.
*.md
!README.md

# Logs / runlogs / DBs / scratch
*.log
*.db
_runlog/
*.bak
*.tmp
*.swp
notes-local.md

# Python / editor caches
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/

# KEPT for the run (small): build/*.py, research/*.py, *.md docs,
# data/sector_config.json, data/it_census_universe.csv, data/_jpx_data_j.xls,
# data/quarterly/_all_it_targets_*.json, .env.example, .gitignore

# Accidental nested duplicate folder (quite_change/quite_change/)
/quite_change/
